<section id="about" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">About pFAwS</h2>
    <p class="section-copy">
      pFAwS is a professional wrestling management simulation focused on belief, reaction, consequence, and long-term history. The player runs a wrestling federation over time, shaping cards, talent relationships, contracts, developmental pipelines, territory expansion, and business survival.
    </p>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="panel card">
        <h3>What the player does</h3>
        <ul class="clean">
          <li>Book matches, promos, and shows</li>
          <li>Manage rosters, staff, managers, and free agents</li>
          <li>Negotiate contracts with leverage, promises, and clauses</li>
          <li>Handle creative refusal, release disputes, and legal pressure</li>
          <li>Grow territories and plan cities, venues, and events</li>
          <li>Develop talent through The Forge Academy</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="panel card">
        <h3>Design rules</h3>
        <ul class="clean">
          <li>Everything should be moddable wherever practical</li>
          <li>Every major system should eventually have its own screen</li>
          <li>UI should read projections, not mutate simulation truth directly</li>
          <li>Math and consequences should be explained in plain English</li>
          <li>Long saves should stay clean through history archiving</li>
          <li>Advanced systems should remain optional when possible</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="veritos" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Veritos System</h2>
    <p class="section-copy">
      Veritos means <strong>“The Truth of the Spirit.”</strong> It is the core simulation doctrine of pFAwS. Wrestling may be staged, but audience reaction, momentum, trust, fallout, and belief still become measurable truths inside the game.
    </p>
    <div class="quote">The punches may not be real. The crowd’s belief is.</div>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
      <article class="panel card">
        <h3>Simulation law flow</h3>
        <p><strong>State → Registry → Resolver → Delta → Mutated State</strong></p>
        <p>
          Systems read the current truth-state, resolve reactions, apply deltas, and produce a new mutated truth the rest of the simulation must respect.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="panel card">
        <h3>Why it matters</h3>
        <p>
          pFAwS does not treat wrestling as a simple HP exchange. Moves, promos, refusals, betrayals, chants, and finishes matter because of what they change in the state of the world and how the crowd receives them.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
      <article class="panel card">
        <h3>Crowd belief</h3>
        <p>Belief is not flavor text. It affects momentum, reaction, trust, and future creative reality.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="panel card">
        <h3>Explainable math</h3>
        <p>Every major system should explain what happened and why in readable language.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="panel card">
        <h3>Shared truth</h3>
        <p>UI, history, and projections should all reflect one simulation truth instead of competing versions.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

