  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Devlog</h2>
    <p class="section-copy">
      The devlog is where development notes, system deep dives, and grounded progress reports should live. The goal is to document what is built, what is changing, and what is still unfinished without pretending the project is further along than it is.
    </p>
    <div class="devlog-list">
      <article class="devlog-post">
        <div class="post-meta">Draft Post</div>
        <h3>Building Veritos: The Crowd Belief Engine</h3>
        <p>
          Professional wrestling is difficult to simulate honestly because visible action is only part of what matters. Veritos begins from the idea that crowd belief is a real, measurable force inside the promotion. Acceptance, rejection, momentum, backlash, and trust should all become state the game can react to.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="devlog-post">
        <div class="post-meta">Future Topics</div>
        <p>A–Z integration, negotiation leverage, explainable simulation screens, history archiving, and mod support direction.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

